<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-06-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-06-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="155" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">840.50 Recovery/6–1947:
                                    Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <seg rendition="#left">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                        <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">urgent</hi>
                                    </seg>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-06-19">June 19,
                                            1947</date>.</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>2440. The British tell me that they have “a firm verbal
                                    commitment” from the French that they will go along with them
                                    even if the Soviets refuse the invitation to participate in the
                                    conversations. They showed me a tentative agenda listing the
                                    “form and nature of American aid” in order of importance: <list>
                                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">a</hi>)</label>
                                        <item>Supply of raw materials, foodstuffs and animal
                                            feeds.</item>
                                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">b</hi>)</label>
                                        <item>Supply of equipment and means of production.</item>
                                        <label>(<hi rend="italic">c</hi>)</label>
                                        <item>Financial credits.</item>
                                    </list>
                                </p>
                                <p>Duff Cooper<note n="1" xml:id="d155fn1">Alfred Duff Cooper,
                                        British Ambassador in France.</note> expects the Ministers
                                    to meet again next week.</p>
                                <p>Repeated to London as 459, sent Department 2440.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>